measures.name: resize_existing_windows_to_match_a_given_wwr
measures.display_name: Resize existing windows to match a given WWR
measures.description:
This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface
measures.modeler_description:
The measure works in several steps:

1. Find the current Window to Wall Ratio (WWR).
This will compute the WWR by taking into account all of the surfaces that have all of the following characteristics:
- They are walls
- They have the outside boundary condition as 'Outdoors' (aims to not take into account the adiabatic surfaces)
- They are SunExposed (could be removed...)

2. Resize all of the existing windows by re-setting the vertices: scaled centered on centroid.

If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface

measures.name: reduce_lighting_loads_by_percentage
measures.description: The lighting system in this building uses more power per area than is required with the latest lighting technologies.  Replace the lighting system with a newer, more efficient lighting technology.  Newer technologies provide the same amount of light but use less energy in the process.
measures.modeler_description: This measure supports models which have a mixture of lighting assigned to spaces and space types.  The lighting may be specified as individual luminaires, lighting equipment level, lighting power per area, or lighting power per person. Loop through all lights and luminaires in the specified space type or the entire building. Clone the definition if it is shared by other lights, rename and adjust the power based on the specified percentage. Link the new definition to the existing lights or luminaire instance.  Adjust the power for lighting equipment assigned to a particular space but only if that space is part of the selected space type by  looping through the objects first in space types and then in spaces, but again only for spaces that are in the specified space type (unless the entire building has been chosen).  Material and installation cost increases will be applied to all costs related to both the definition and instance of the lighting object.  If this measure includes baseline costs, then the material and installation costs of the lighting objects in the baseline model will be summed together and added as a capital cost on the building object.

measures.name: openstudio_results
measures.description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.
measures.modeler_description: For the most part consumption data comes from the tabular EnergyPlus results, however there are a few requests added for time series results. Space type and loop details come from the OpenStudio model. The code for this is modular, making it easy to use as a template for your own custom reports. The structure of the report uses bootstrap, and the graphs use dimple js. The new measure warning section will show warnings generated by upstream measures. It will not show forward translation warnings, EnergyPlus warnings, or warnings that might be reported by this measure.

datapoints.name: R-99 Window Alternative

da_descriptions.name: R-99 Window Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: Replaces the construction of all surface & sub surface objects matching a specified construction with new construction. The construction to replace with must already exist in the model.

da_descriptions.name: resize_existing_windows_to_match_a_given_wwr
da_descriptions.description:
This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface

da_descriptions.name: reduce_lighting_loads_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: The lighting system in this building uses more power per area than is required with the latest lighting technologies.  Replace the lighting system with a newer, more efficient lighting technology.  Newer technologies provide the same amount of light but use less energy in the process.

da_descriptions.name: reduce_space_infiltration_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: This measure will reduce space infiltration rates by the requested percentage. A cost per square foot of building area can be added to the model.

da_descriptions.name: SI Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.

steps.description: Option 1 Description: Replaces the construction of all surface & sub surface objects matching a specified construction with new construction. The construction to replace with must already exist in the model.
steps.name: R-99 Window Option

result.step_final_condition: The building finished with 0 surface(s) and 11 sub surface(s) construction replaced with R-99 Window.
result.step_initial_condition: The building started with 0 surface(s) and 11 sub surface(s) having construction: ASHRAE 189.1-2009 ExtWindow ClimateZone alt-res 4-5.

steps.description:
This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface
steps.name: resize_existing_windows_to_match_a_given_wwr

result.measure_display_name: Resize existing windows to match a given WWR

steps.description: The lighting system in this building uses more power per area than is required with the latest lighting technologies.  Replace the lighting system with a newer, more efficient lighting technology.  Newer technologies provide the same amount of light but use less energy in the process.
steps.name: reduce_lighting_loads_by_percentage

steps.description: This measure will reduce space infiltration rates by the requested percentage. A cost per square foot of building area can be added to the model.
steps.name: reduce_space_infiltration_by_percentage

steps.description: Option 1 Description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.

datapoints.name: R-99 Exterior Wall Alternative

da_descriptions.name: R-99 Wall Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 2 Description: Replaces the construction of all surface & sub surface objects matching a specified construction with new construction. The construction to replace with must already exist in the model.

da_descriptions.name: resize_existing_windows_to_match_a_given_wwr
da_descriptions.description:
This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface

da_descriptions.name: reduce_lighting_loads_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: The lighting system in this building uses more power per area than is required with the latest lighting technologies.  Replace the lighting system with a newer, more efficient lighting technology.  Newer technologies provide the same amount of light but use less energy in the process.

da_descriptions.name: reduce_space_infiltration_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: This measure will reduce space infiltration rates by the requested percentage. A cost per square foot of building area can be added to the model.

da_descriptions.name: SI Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.

datapoints.name: R-99 Roof Alternative

da_descriptions.name: R-99 Roof Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 3 Description: Replaces the construction of all surface & sub surface objects matching a specified construction with new construction. The construction to replace with must already exist in the model.

da_descriptions.name: resize_existing_windows_to_match_a_given_wwr
da_descriptions.description:
This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface

da_descriptions.name: reduce_lighting_loads_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: The lighting system in this building uses more power per area than is required with the latest lighting technologies.  Replace the lighting system with a newer, more efficient lighting technology.  Newer technologies provide the same amount of light but use less energy in the process.

da_descriptions.name: reduce_space_infiltration_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: This measure will reduce space infiltration rates by the requested percentage. A cost per square foot of building area can be added to the model.

da_descriptions.name: SI Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.

steps.description: Option 3 Description: Replaces the construction of all surface & sub surface objects matching a specified construction with new construction. The construction to replace with must already exist in the model.
steps.name: R-99 Roof Option

result.step_final_condition: The building finished with 12 surface(s) and 0 sub surface(s) construction replaced with R-99 Roof.
result.step_initial_condition: The building started with 12 surface(s) and 0 sub surface(s) having construction: ASHRAE 189.1-2009 ExtRoof IEAD ClimateZone 2-5.

steps.description:
This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface
steps.name: resize_existing_windows_to_match_a_given_wwr

result.measure_display_name: Resize existing windows to match a given WWR

steps.description: The lighting system in this building uses more power per area than is required with the latest lighting technologies.  Replace the lighting system with a newer, more efficient lighting technology.  Newer technologies provide the same amount of light but use less energy in the process.
steps.name: reduce_lighting_loads_by_percentage

steps.description: This measure will reduce space infiltration rates by the requested percentage. A cost per square foot of building area can be added to the model.
steps.name: reduce_space_infiltration_by_percentage

steps.description: Option 1 Description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.
steps.name: SI Option

datapoints.name: R-99 Floor Alternative

da_descriptions.name: R-99 Floor Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 4 Description: Replaces the construction of all surface & sub surface objects matching a specified construction with new construction. The construction to replace with must already exist in the model.

da_descriptions.name: resize_existing_windows_to_match_a_given_wwr
da_descriptions.description:
This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface

da_descriptions.name: reduce_lighting_loads_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: The lighting system in this building uses more power per area than is required with the latest lighting technologies.  Replace the lighting system with a newer, more efficient lighting technology.  Newer technologies provide the same amount of light but use less energy in the process.

da_descriptions.name: reduce_space_infiltration_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: This measure will reduce space infiltration rates by the requested percentage. A cost per square foot of building area can be added to the model.

da_descriptions.name: SI Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.

datapoints.name: No Window Alternative

da_descriptions.name: replace_surface_construction
da_descriptions.description: Replaces the construction of all surface & sub surface objects matching a specified construction with new construction. The construction to replace with must already exist in the model.

da_descriptions.name: 1% WWR Option
da_descriptions.description:
Option 1 Description: This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface

da_descriptions.name: reduce_lighting_loads_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: The lighting system in this building uses more power per area than is required with the latest lighting technologies.  Replace the lighting system with a newer, more efficient lighting technology.  Newer technologies provide the same amount of light but use less energy in the process.

da_descriptions.name: reduce_space_infiltration_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: This measure will reduce space infiltration rates by the requested percentage. A cost per square foot of building area can be added to the model.

da_descriptions.name: SI Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.

steps.description: Replaces the construction of all surface & sub surface objects matching a specified construction with new construction. The construction to replace with must already exist in the model.
steps.name: replace_surface_construction

steps.description:
Option 1 Description: This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface
steps.name: 1% WWR Option

result.measure_display_name: Resize existing windows to match a given WWR

datapoints.name: No Lighting Alternative

da_descriptions.name: replace_surface_construction
da_descriptions.description: Replaces the construction of all surface & sub surface objects matching a specified construction with new construction. The construction to replace with must already exist in the model.

da_descriptions.name: resize_existing_windows_to_match_a_given_wwr
da_descriptions.description:
This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface

da_descriptions.name: No Lighting Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: The lighting system in this building uses more power per area than is required with the latest lighting technologies.  Replace the lighting system with a newer, more efficient lighting technology.  Newer technologies provide the same amount of light but use less energy in the process.

da_descriptions.name: reduce_space_infiltration_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: This measure will reduce space infiltration rates by the requested percentage. A cost per square foot of building area can be added to the model.

da_descriptions.name: SI Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.

datapoints.name: No Infiltration Alternative

da_descriptions.name: replace_surface_construction
da_descriptions.description: Replaces the construction of all surface & sub surface objects matching a specified construction with new construction. The construction to replace with must already exist in the model.

da_descriptions.name: resize_existing_windows_to_match_a_given_wwr
da_descriptions.description:
This measure aims to resize all of the existing windows in order to produce a specified, user-input, window to wall ratio.
The windows will be resized around their centroid.
It should be noted that this measure should work in all cases when DOWNSIZING the windows (which is often the need given the 40% WWR imposed as baseline by ASHRAE Appendix G).
If you aim to increase the area, please note that this could result in subsurfaces being larger than their parent surface

da_descriptions.name: reduce_lighting_loads_by_percentage
da_descriptions.description: The lighting system in this building uses more power per area than is required with the latest lighting technologies.  Replace the lighting system with a newer, more efficient lighting technology.  Newer technologies provide the same amount of light but use less energy in the process.

da_descriptions.name: No Infiltration Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: This measure will reduce space infiltration rates by the requested percentage. A cost per square foot of building area can be added to the model.

da_descriptions.name: SI Option
da_descriptions.description: Option 1 Description: This measure creates high level tables and charts pulling both from model inputs and EnergyPlus results. It has building level information as well as detail on space types, thermal zones, HVAC systems, envelope characteristics, and economics. Click the heading above a chart to view a table of the chart data.
